A pre-polling day message from your North Down Alliance candidate Dr. Stephen Farry - 

'The General Election on Thursday will be absolutely critical to determining the future direction for both Northern Ireland and the wider UK.
 
Brexit lies at the heart of this election. There is a huge decision for the next Parliament to make. I want to be your MP who joins with many others in giving the people of the UK the chance to have their say again on the final deal, with the option to Remain on the ballot.
 
Yet, this election is about so much more. It is about sending a signal to get the Assembly restored, and in particular to fix the ever deepening crisis in our health service, plus accelerating how we tackle Climate Change.
 
Lady Hermon has been a great servant over the past 18 years. It is important that North Down continues to be represented by an MP that is progressive, inclusive and pro-European. The DUP don‚Äôt reflect the values of this constituency.
 
I have served the North Down area through different elected office, including as Minister for Employment & Learning.
 
With North Down now a straight contest between the DUP and me, I would be very grateful for your support on Thursday.'
